The Governor of Adamawa State, Ahamdu Fintiri on Wednesday emerged as the gubernatorial candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in the state following the governorship primaries. Chairman of the PDP Governorship Primaries Committee, Barr. Gavin Katabs who made the announcement said Governor Fintri polled 663 of the 668 votes, with five of the votes declared invalidated. It could be recalled that Fintiri, former Speaker of Adamawa State Assembly and his Deputy, Serth Crowder, were sworn in for their first term on May 29, 2019, on the platform of the party -Advertisement- More details later…